OL,3,CFather's campaign after finding wife
OL,4,Cdead at home
OL,6,FWhen Mr Lockwood returned home that
OL,7,Fnight, he initially assumed his wife
OL,8,Fwas asleep, but knew something "wasn't
OL,9,Fright" when he saw her.
OL,11,FHe rang emergency services, saying:
OL,12,F"The, adrenaline and disbelief kick
OL,13,Fin."
OL,15,FHe said telling his eldest son Arthur
OL,16,Fwas "the hardest thing he would ever
OL,17,Fdo".
OL,19,F"He just sobbed, he was only three at
OL,20,Fthe time but he knew" he said.
